This paper is about information retrieval (IR) evaluation, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of graded relevance assessments and measures in IR evaluation, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as text classification and sentiment analysis. Therefore, it could also be classified under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Deep Learning (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper discusses evaluation measures, which could fall under Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as well.
